<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF686AD7FCDE93231DF7BC76" pageId="147" pageNumber="908" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF686AD7FCDE93231DF7BC76" blockId="147.[801,1395,1315,1742]" lastBlockId="147.[184,1395,1748,3282]" pageId="147" pageNumber="908">
Based on limited genetic data, M. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF686AD7FABB93231D86BE88" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1872" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="908" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucogaster">leucogaster</taxonomicName>
appears to be closely related to M. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF686AD7FCAC93981DA1BED0" box="[848,929,1473,1506]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="908" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bicolor">bicolor</taxonomicName>
, M. rongjiangensis, M. fanjingshanensis, and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF686AD7FC5293B41A73BD38" authorityName="Eger &amp; Lim" authorityYear="2011" box="[942,1139,1517,1546]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="908" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shuipuensis">M. shuipuensis</taxonomicName>
. M. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF686AD7FB4893B41B3CBD38" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1872" box="[1204,1340,1517,1546]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="908" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucogaster">leucogaster</taxonomicName>
was previously considered to include 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF686AD7FB0D90491D5DBD6A" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1880" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="909" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hilgendorfi">M. hilgendorfi</taxonomicName>
as a race, but genetic and morphological data support their treatment as separate species. Race rubex was treated as a distinct species by Kuo Haochih and colleagues in 2009, but it is based only on a single specimen and the only 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF686AD7FB7B908D1AD9BDC7" authorityName="J. E. Gray" authorityYear="1844" box="[1159,1241,1748,1781]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nyctophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="908" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">major</taxonomicName>
difference is where the foot attaches to the ankle (generally a good way for distinguishing 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF686AD7FAF190A51F24BC76" pageId="147" pageNumber="908">Murina species</taxonomicName>
); further study needed. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
